Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly elevated ALT, indicating possible mild liver involvement. Chloride is slightly above normal but likely not clinically significant. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, proteins, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal function.
